// @test regression/INV054-two-level-namespace-local-scope
// @description strategy.risk.* may only be declared in global scope; TV emits CE10188 "Cannot use ... in local scope" (probed all six 2026-06-10). We previously accepted them anywhere because the callee name-resolver only handled single-level `ns.member` member chains, so two-level builtin names (strategy.risk.*, strategy.opentrades.*, chart.point.*) resolved to "" and skipped ALL validation. See investigations/INV054-two-level-namespace-resolution/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, column=5, message="Function 'strategy.risk.max_drawdown' cannot be called from a local scope. It must be called from the global scope."
//@version=6
strategy("t")
if close > open
    strategy.risk.max_drawdown(90, strategy.percent_of_equity)
plot(close)
